They really are good.

00:35:00.060 --> 00:35:04.500
And the wrapping up, we always
thought, when we had discovery

00:35:04.500 --> 00:35:06.760 position:56%
of penicillin, that we had the magic
bullet and we were not going to have

00:35:06.760 --> 00:35:10.870
to deal with any kind of infections
again; but that's not true.

00:35:10.870 --> 00:35:12.360
Because even Sir Alexander
Fleming --

00:35:12.360 --> 00:35:16.400
discovery of penicillin also
receiving the Nobel Prize,

00:35:16.400 --> 00:35:21.020
cautioned resistance is a natural
counterpart to antibiotics.

00:35:21.020 --> 00:35:23.170
Welcome to the world of microbes.

00:35:23.170 --> 00:35:27.260
And this now, once again, is
an international global issue.

00:35:27.260 --> 00:35:30.130
Over the past decade, I think
we've seen some major concerns.

00:35:30.130 --> 00:35:33.600
Nothing could be more heartbreaking
than to have an infection

00:35:33.600 --> 00:35:36.660
and to have the physician tell
you, "I'm so sorry, I have nothing

00:35:36.660 --> 00:35:38.660
to treat you or your family with."

00:35:38.660 --> 00:35:42.830
And even more heartbreaking to
see that member of the family die.

00:35:42.830 --> 00:35:46.170
So this is not to be taken
lightly; it's very serious.

00:35:46.170 --> 00:35:48.850
And we all have to be involved.

00:35:48.850 --> 00:35:51.610
Are we capable of developing
some new antibiotics?

00:35:51.610 --> 00:35:54.210
For the longest time
after this development,

00:35:54.210 --> 00:35:55.510
we didn't think we needed them.

00:35:55.510 --> 00:35:57.560
They focused on virology
and vaccines.

00:35:57.560 --> 00:36:02.070
Now come fast forward, we
don't have in the armamentarium

00:36:02.070 --> 00:36:05.570
of drugs a lot of new antibiotics.

00:36:05.570 --> 00:36:11.360
So as we understand the genome
of the microbe, are there ways

00:36:11.360 --> 00:36:13.350
that we can come up with new
development of procedures

00:36:13.350 --> 00:36:16.950
to treat these particular microbes?

00:36:16.950 --> 00:36:20.870
This brings us all together:
public health, agriculture,

00:36:20.870 --> 00:36:23.260
research, national security.

00:36:23.260 --> 00:36:25.070
I mentioned it earlier,
it's so true,

00:36:25.070 --> 00:36:29.330
international travel has
really opened up the capability

00:36:29.330 --> 00:36:32.490
of having these microbes
and the resistance

00:36:32.490 --> 00:36:35.390
that they carry come over here.

00:36:35.390 --> 00:36:38.840
You could have an injury
when you're walking in India

00:36:38.840 --> 00:36:42.180
and get an infection, and come
back home here and all of a sudden,

00:36:42.180 --> 00:36:44.020
boom, you have an infection.

00:36:44.020 --> 00:36:45.320
And guess what?

00:36:45.320 --> 00:36:48.360
It's a microbe and we don't have
that particular to treat it with.

00:36:48.360 --> 00:36:50.990
That's devastating, and
that has actually happened.

00:36:50.990 --> 00:36:55.720
So we do need to be very cautious
and we all have to be stewards --

00:36:55.720 --> 00:36:58.560
when I say stewards -- of
how we use these products,

00:36:58.560 --> 00:37:01.100
be it for our own health,
taking care of our kids,

00:37:01.100 --> 00:37:02.400
taking care of our animals.

00:37:02.400 --> 00:37:05.330
And more importantly, major
changes that I'm very proud

00:37:05.330 --> 00:37:11.080
of at FDA is we really [inaudible]
in the case of how historically,

00:37:11.080 --> 00:37:13.410
some very important
antimicrobials were being used

00:37:13.410 --> 00:37:15.310
in production agriculture.

00:37:15.310 --> 00:37:19.410
Way back when, some of our food
animals received these products

00:37:19.410 --> 00:37:20.710
and they seemed to do very well.

00:37:20.710 --> 00:37:24.840
They grew, they stayed
healthy -- well, that's nice.

00:37:24.840 --> 00:37:27.260
But that definition is
not good enough today.

00:37:27.260 --> 00:37:29.720
You need to know why are
you using an antibiotic,

00:37:29.720 --> 00:37:33.680
what species is it being used
in, what dose range, how long,

00:37:33.680 --> 00:37:35.590
and what pathogen are you treating.

00:37:35.590 --> 00:37:39.110
And it really needs to be
properly handled through physicians

00:37:39.110 --> 00:37:41.620
for people and for
veterinarians for animals.

00:37:41.620 --> 00:37:44.860
And so now we have made those
changes and we're seeing all

00:37:44.860 --> 00:37:47.030
of that happen with a proper label.

00:37:47.030 --> 00:37:50.870
And by January 2017 on
the food animal side,

00:37:50.870 --> 00:37:53.140
any of these medically
important antibiotics will

00:37:53.140 --> 00:37:54.790
in fact have proper labels.

00:37:54.790 --> 00:37:58.200 position:56%
And the idea of thinking they could
have been used for growth promotion,

00:37:58.200 --> 00:38:00.460
feed efficiency will
not happen anymore.

00:38:00.460 --> 00:38:02.860
So again, there needs
to be very cautious use

00:38:02.860 --> 00:38:05.180
of these very important products.

00:38:06.960 --> 00:38:10.840
Along those lines, we did have
an executive order to try to come

00:38:10.840 --> 00:38:14.410
